text.tspan: Note: Shown is the ‘period life expectancy’. This is the average number of years a newborn would
live if age-specific mortality rates in the current year were to stay the same throughout its life.
Data source: UN WPP (2022); Zijdeman et al. (2015); Riley (2005)
